Kids Privacy Policy
Kids Privacy Policy
W3villa Technologies, also referred to as ‘we’, ‘us’, ‘our’, manages the website ‘www.studio.w3villa.com’. We specialize in developing kids’ learning applications (‘apps’) for mobile devices. When we mention ‘you’ or ‘your’, we mean anyone using our apps.
W3villa Technologies is committed to protecting the privacy and security of our users. We understand the sensitivity of the concern about information and safety measures. We are also very much aware of taking the necessary steps on data security and information and that’s why we would like you to know about the safety measures to keep our application secured. This Privacy policy gives you detailed information on how we collect information and how we are using the data.
Compliance
Our kids’ learning application complies with relevant privacy laws. We ensure to protect the personal information and online privacy of users and we keep sharing the information with parents to take an active role in protecting their children’s privacy online by checking the information that is being collected.
The application does not collect information purposely as defined by privacy laws from users under the age of consent. If we find any information we collected that is against the violation, we remove it permanently and do not participate again.
We do include links to external activities in our kids’ apps, such as rate us, view our other apps, links for worksheets, and social media page links. These are all protected inside of sections of the app only parents can access by solving a childproof puzzle.
We are very much concerned about the safety and privacy of your children. If you have any queries or inputs about how we are collecting information, please contact us at the below email address.
The information we collect:
– We collect information from you to ensure that the data will not be used for any personal use and if you contact us regarding any query about the data, we will remove it and will not use it further.
– For tracking data, we use third-party analytics to monitor the traffic and users’ behavior. Also, we check how users engage with our site. You can find the unity analytics privacy policy here:
https://unity.com/legal/privacy-policy
How do we protect the information?
We take the necessary steps to keep confidential and secure the information we collect from our users, although we do not collect personal information about users.
Disclosure of information from outside parties
We follow a simple and easy process to secure the information on our server. As we are not collecting any personal information from users, there is no way to disclose the data outside. Although we may display aggregate statistics, we do not disclose any personal information.
Languages currently planned for our learning app:
English
Hindi
